		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />OK so in the end, I guess since we have no way of knowing if the unused pins on +5V or GND are unued /CE or /OE signals or not, the logic would say we should show the names of the singal leading to the pin.
<br />
<br />However, it seems more complicated to do it this way as it implies different pinouts for PRG and CHR.
<br />
<br />The other way to go, would be to make pinouts with only the name of the signals, that is "Ax", "Dx", "CE", "/CE", "/OE", and that's all. Unused signals would be still specified as "+5V" or "GND" as we can't be very sure of their usage.
<br />
<br />Because on most carts the /CE and /OE wiring is the same, a simple paragraph about it should be used, and exeptions (such as AOROM) should be mentionned next to the pinout (like it's already right now).

		

		</td>
	</tr>
